(487, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers can also employ silicon carbide (SiC) tubes as heat exchange tubes. SiC is a ceramic material known for its excellent mechanical and thermal properties, including high strength, hardness, thermal conductivity, as well as good corrosion and high-temperature resistance.One significant advantage of silicon carbide tubes is their ability to withstand extremely high temperatures up to 1650°C (3000°F), making them suitable for high-temperature applications such as chemical processing and metallurgy. They are also highly resistant to corrosion from acids, alkalis, and other corrosive fluids, making them well-suited for use with corrosive process fluids.\",\"id\":\"2\",\"en_title\":\"Why are silicon carbide tubes used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684916410),
(488, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers can utilize glass lining tubes as heat exchange tubes due to their excellent chemical and thermal properties. Glass lining is a protective layer applied to the inner surface of the tubes, acting as a barrier between corrosive process fluids and the metal tubes. It provides enhanced resistance to corrosion and erosion, making it particularly suitable for handling corrosive fluids such as acids, alkalis, or salt solutions. Additionally, glass lining tubes exhibit good thermal conductivity, facilitating efficient heat transfer between process fluids and the heat exchange medium. This makes them highly suitable for applications where heat transfer efficiency is crucial, including chemical processing, pharmaceuticals, and food and beverage production. Using glass lining tubes in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers offers advantages such as improved durability, extended lifespan, and enhanced heat transfer performance, resulting in reduced maintenance and operating costs.\",\"id\":\"3\",\"en_title\":\"Why are glass lining tubes used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684916443),
(489, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Tube sheets are crucial components of shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers, providing support for heat exchange tubes and acting as seals between the shell and tube sides. To ensure excellent corrosion resistance and mechanical strength, steel-lined molded PFA is commonly used as the lining material for tube sheets.PFA, a perfluoroalkoxy polymer, is known for its excellent chemical and thermal properties, including high corrosion resistance, high-temperature resistance, and mechanical stress resistance. It is also highly resistant to creep, stress cracking, and fatigue, making it well-suited for demanding applications such as chemical processing.In the steel-lined, molded PFA process, a layer of PFA is applied to the surface of a steel plate using molding techniques. The PFA is heated to a high temperature and then coated onto the steel substrate. This process ensures that the PFA adheres tightly to the steel, providing excellent resistance to chemical corrosion and mechanical stress.By using steel-lined molded PFA for tube sheets, shell and tube shell and tube heat exchanger manufacturers can ensure outstanding corrosion resistance and mechanical strength, resulting in extended lifespan and reduced maintenance and replacement costs.\",\"id\":\"4\",\"en_title\":\"Why are steel-lined, molded PFA used for tube sheets in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684916577),
(490, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"1.The presence of solid particles or fibers in the fluid can accumulate and cause blockages within the pipes. In such cases, considering the use of filters or screens to remove solid particles or fibers can help reduce sedimentation within the pipes. 2.If the fluid has high viscosity, it increases the flow resistance, making it difficult for the fluid to pass through the pipes. In this situation, adjusting the fluid&#039;s temperature or using a heater to reduce its viscosity may be considered. Alternatively, using larger diameter pipes or reducing the pipe length can help minimize the flow resistance. 3.Corrosion or deposits may be present on the internal surface of the pipes within the shell and tube shell and tube heat exchanger, leading to blockages. In this case, using cleaning agents or mechanical brushes to clean the inner walls of the pipes can help reduce the accumulation of deposits. 4.Another possible reason could be improper pipe design or the use of unsuitable pipe materials for the fluid characteristics, resulting in poor fluid flow or easy sediment accumulation. In such cases, redesigning the pipes or replacing the pipe materials may be necessary to ensure smooth fluid flow.\",\"id\":\"5\",\"en_title\":\"Why is your shell and tube shell and tube heat exchanger frequently getting clogged?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684916647),
(491, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Electric welding can be used to repair leaks in metal shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers because it provides a strong and permanent bond between the damaged metal surfaces. The process involves melting the metal at the damaged point using an electric arc and then allowing it to solidify and fuse with the surrounding metal. One advantage of electric welding is that it can be used for on-site repair of leaks without the need to remove the entire shell and tube heat exchanger from the process pipeline. This can save time and money compared to replacing the entire shell and tube heat exchanger or sending it off-site for repair. However, it should be noted that electric welding may not be suitable for all types of shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers or all types of leaks. For example, if the shell and tube heat exchanger is made of materials such as titanium or zirconium that are difficult to weld, electric welding may not be a feasible repair option. Additionally, if the leak is located in a critical area of the shell and tube heat exchanger or is too large to be repaired through welding, other repair or replacement options may need to be considered. It is important to ensure that the electric welding process is performed by qualified and experienced welders, and appropriate safety measures should be taken to prevent injury or damage to the shell and tube shell and tube heat exchanger during the repair process.\",\"id\":\"6\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\",\"en_title\":\"Why does your metal shell and tube shell and tube heat exchanger continue to leak even after being repaired with electric welding?\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684916689);
