(514, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Industries that require highly resistant shell and tube heat exchangers for corrosive applications can consider purchasing glass-lined or silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers. These industries may include chemical processing, pharmaceuticals, petrochemicals, food and beverage production, among others, which often involve the use of highly corrosive substances in their manufacturing processes. In the chemical processing industry, glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers can be used for reactions involving acids, alkalis, and other corrosive substances. They are also employed in the pharmaceutical industry for the production of drugs and other products that require highly sterile conditions. silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers are commonly used in applications that require high temperatures, such as crude oil refining or in the production of ceramics and glass. They are also used in the semiconductor industry for producing high-purity silicon wafers. In summary, glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers can be employed in a range of industrial applications that require highly resistant equipment, but it is essential to carefully assess the specific requirements of the application and consult with shell and tube heat exchanger experts to determine the best material and design that suits your needs.\",\"id\":\"27\",\"en_title\":\"What kind of industries would purchase glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917558),
(515, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"To persuade potential customers to choose glass-lined or silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers instead of traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers, you can focus on the benefits offered by these materials. Some potential advantages include: Corrosion resistance: glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers exhibit high resistance to corrosion, making them ideal for applications involving acidic or corrosive media. Longer lifespan: Due to their corrosion resistance, glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers typically have a longer lifespan compared to traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers. Improved efficiency: glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers have increased resistance to fouling and scaling, reducing the likelihood of blockages or the need for frequent cleaning. This enhances efficiency and lowers maintenance costs. Reduced downtime: glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers may require less downtime for maintenance and repairs, resulting in lower production costs and increased productivity. You can also provide case studies or examples of successful applications of these shell and tube heat exchangers and emphasize the quality and reliability of the products. By providing this information and showcasing the advantages of glass-lined and silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers to potential customers, you may be able to persuade them to choose these materials to meet their shell and tube heat exchanger needs.\",\"id\":\"28\",\"en_title\":\"Most shell and tube heat exchanger purchasers in the market choose shell and tube heat exchangers made of metal materials. How can I guide them to choose glass-lined or silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917604),
(516, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"According to market research, glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers are widely used in China, particularly in the pharmaceutical and chemical industries. They are also used in some other countries, including India, Japan, and South Korea. However, in other regions of the world such as North America and Europe, the use of glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers is not as common. The usage of silicon carbide shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers is also relatively limited compared to traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers. \",\"id\":\"29\",\"en_title\":\"Which countries around the world have a higher frequency of glass-lined shell and tube heat exchanger procurement?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917634),
(517, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers may not be as popular in North America and Europe compared to other regions for several reasons: Limited awareness: The use of glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers may not be widely known in certain markets due to limited marketing and promotion by manufacturers. Higher cost: glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers may have higher upfront costs compared to traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers. This reduces their attractiveness for companies that prioritize cost savings. Limited availability: In some markets, the supply chain for glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers may not be as well-established, making it more challenging for companies to purchase and maintain these products. Different regulations and standards: Different markets may have varying regulations and standards that can impact the use and sale of glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers. Different industrial practices: Industrial practices and preferences may vary by region, and traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers may be more common or preferred in certain markets. Compared to other regions of the world, there are several reasons why glass-lined shell and tube &amp;nbsp;heat exchangers are not widely popular in North America and Europe. Firstly, some countries have strict regulations regarding the use of glass-lined equipment due to concerns about potential leaching of glass into products, which can pose health hazards. In North America and Europe, regulatory authorities require extensive testing and certification before approving the use of glass-lined equipment, which can increase production and purchasing costs. Secondly, glass-lined equipment tends to have more complex designs and structures compared to traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers. This can result in higher manufacturing, repair, and maintenance costs, which may deter some buyers from considering them. Lastly, the preference for traditional metal shell and tube heat exchangers in North America and Europe may be attributed to their long-standing use and established supply chains, making them easier to obtain and more cost-effective.\",\"id\":\"30\",\"en_title\":\"Why are glass-lined shell and tube heat exchangers not widely popular in North America and Europe?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917675),
(518, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers are used in various industries worldwide, but due to their higher cost, they are not as widely used as traditional metal shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers. However, silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers are often preferred in applications with highly corrosive environments, such as in the chemical and pharmaceutical industries. Some countries where silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers may be more commonly used include the United States, Germany, Japan, and China.\",\"id\":\"31\",\"en_title\":\"Which countries around the world have a higher frequency of silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchanger procurement?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917730),
