(520, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/add', 'faq-添加', '{\"enable\":\"1\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Enamel (glass-lined) shell and tube heat exchangers are commonly used in the chemical and pharmaceutical industries. They are well-suited for handling corrosive and abrasive media such as acids, alkalis, and salts. They are also frequently employed in food and beverage processing, particularly for heating and cooling temperature-sensitive liquids. silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers are typically used in applications that involve high temperatures and pressure differentials, such as the petrochemical and power generation industries. They are also suitable for handling corrosive and abrasive fluids and are commonly used in heat transfer processes for chemical and polymer production. The specific media that are best suited for either glass-lined or silicon carbide shell and tube heat exchangers depend on various factors, including temperature, pressure, chemical composition, and other process parameters. Generally, both types of shell and tube heat exchangers are well-equipped to handle corrosive and abrasive fluids, but each may have specific advantages in certain applications.\",\"id\":\"33\",\"en_title\":\"Which media are more suitable for the use of glass-lined heat exchangers and silicon carbide heat exchangers?\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\"}', '114.217.205.91', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/86.0.4240.198 Safari/537.36', 1684917888),
