(599, 1, 'admin', '/admin/products.Products/edit', 'Unknown(edit)', '{\"id\":\"21\",\"parent_id\":\"1\",\"layout\":\"vertical\",\"name\":\"product_21\",\"en_name\":\"New Type External Glass Lined Shell and Tube Heat Exchanger\",\"desc\":\"\",\"en_desc\":\"\",\"detail\":\"\",\"en_detail\":\"For the external glass lined tubular heat exchanger produced by our company, the outer wall of the shell side and heat exchange tube is coated with glass lined anticorrosive coating. The tube plate is also made of steel lined molded PFA tube plate, sealed with filler threads, sealed with a single piece, and disassembled with a single piece. Compared with the glass lined tubular heat exchanger with material passing through the tube side, due to the large space of the material side, it is more suitable for gas phase materials, which is more conducive to gas saturation, heat exchange and final discharge in the cavity. When the heat exchange medium is used in the tube side, a jacket is also set outside, and the heat exchange medium can also be used in the jacket, so that the materials can fully exchange heat inside and outside. Traditional glass lined floating head tubular heat exchanger generally adopts glass lined tube sheet explosive enamel or PTFE tube sheet, which is easy to leak in case of high-pressure working condition, high maintenance cost, and too troublesome to disassemble and assemble. The same heat exchange area is larger. Compared with traditional glass lined floating head tubular heat exchanger, it is more resistant to pressure, and it is not easy to shake and indunce enamel bursting when gas enters. It also saves the user&#039;s use cost.\",\"image_small\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230526\\/011659de709185512a42952330e5d69def272473.png\",\"image_mid\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230426\\/83f0684ba3fb6a0314a07d6f0ec8b362e17bc86f.png\",\"image_large\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230423\\/3b23c78834d26beeb7881fb1674764f45932bfbe.png\",\"carousel\":[],\"enable\":\"1\"}', '114.217.196.6', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/108.0.5359.95 Safari/537.36', 1685095640),
(600, 1, 'admin', '/admin/products.Products/edit', 'Unknown(edit)', '{\"id\":\"11\",\"parent_id\":\"1\",\"layout\":\"horizontal\",\"name\":\"\",\"en_name\":\"New Type Shell and Tube Heat Exchanger Coated with Glass-lined Steel\",\"desc\":\"\",\"en_desc\":\"\",\"detail\":\"\",\"en_detail\":\"Wuxi Revivingpicea Machinery Technology Co., Ltd. has designed and developed a new detachable glass lined tubular heat exchanger, which solves such problems of large volume, tube plate enamel bursting, difficult maintenance, damage and easy scrapping on traditional heat exchangers.\\nThe traditional glass lined tubesheet is easy to induce porcerlain bursting due to the stress of its steel billet, especially at the welding point between the tubesheet and the heat exchange tube. Once damaged, the whole set has to be scrapped, which increases the use cost for users. The new detachable glass lined tubular heat exchanger of our company adopts steel lined molded PFA integral tube sheet, discarding the traditional glass lined tube sheet, without the disadvantage of enamel bursting, and adopts a single connection and sealing system, which is more resistant to high temperature and high pressure. The glass lined heat exchange tube can be disassembled and assembled individually. If it is damaged during maintenance, it can be disassembled, assembled and replaced without scrapping the whole set. It is a truly reliable glass lined tubular heat exchanger. Our products are widely used in chemical, pharmaceutical and financial fields, enjoying a good reputation among our customers.\",\"image_small\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230526\\/6c6566689eea420745ed0de1fea6b41b33177948.png\",\"image_mid\":\"\",\"image_large\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230423\\/3b23c78834d26beeb7881fb1674764f45932bfbe.png\",\"carousel\":[],\"enable\":\"1\"}', '114.217.196.6', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/108.0.5359.95 Safari/537.36', 1685095744);
