(623, 1, 'admin', '/admin/products.Products/edit', 'Unknown(edit)', '{\"id\":\"22\",\"parent_id\":\"2\",\"layout\":\"vertical\",\"name\":\"\",\"en_name\":\"New Type Silicon Carbide Shell and Tube Heat Exchanger\",\"desc\":\"\",\"en_desc\":\"\",\"detail\":\"\",\"en_detail\":\"The new silicon carbide tubular heat exchanger that has been presented by our company adopts steel lined molded PFA integral tube sheet. This tube sheet has high material density, no deformation, and stable sealing effect, which better solves the tube sheet sealing problem of traditional silicon carbide heat exchanger. Two sealing structures are designed in one tube sheet, which can seal both the shell side and the tube side on the same tube sheet. If the silicon carbide heat exchanger tube needs to be replaced, just remove the sealing nuts at both ends, pull out the silicon carbide tube, and insert a new silicon carbide tube. It is unneccesary to remove the whole heat exchanger, which greatly reduces the maintenance cost when used on the customer&amp;amp;amp;#039;s site. The shell side of the traditional silicon carbide tubular heat exchanger is made of tetrafluoro baffles. Due to the brittleness of the silicon carbide tube itself, it is easy to break when it shakes under pressure. Our company designed and invented to add a damping plate device to the device. When the silicon carbide tube is under pressure, the risk of shaking and breaking is greatly reduced, and the service life of the heat exchanger can be improved with an increment of heat exchange efficiency.\",\"image_small\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230526\\/ee9da82634b8906a6811b05c29d20523a1c740fb.png\",\"image_mid\":\"\",\"image_large\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230529\\/e01d454e07830e3358f47b29e9ab5410e07c4d60.png\",\"carousel\":[],\"enable\":\"1\"}', '114.217.196.6', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/108.0.5359.95 Safari/537.36', 1685351744),
(624, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/edit', 'faq-编辑', '{\"id\":\"1\",\"enable\":\"1\",\"title\":\"\",\"en_title\":\"Why are glass-lined tubes used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"content\":\"\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Glass-lined tubes are used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube heat exchangers due to several reasons:Corrosion Resistance: Glass lining provides excellent resistance against corrosion from various aggressive fluids, including acids, alkalis, and other corrosive substances. This makes glass-lined tubes ideal for applications where the heat exchanger needs to handle corrosive fluids.Chemical Inertness: Glass is chemically inert, meaning it does not react with the fluids being processed. This ensures that there is no contamination or alteration of the fluid composition, making it suitable for critical processes in industries such as pharmaceuticals, chemicals, and food processing.Smooth Surface: Glass-lined tubes have a smooth surface, which minimizes fouling and scaling. The smoothness prevents the deposition of solids or other contaminants on the tube surface, ensuring efficient heat transfer and reducing the need for frequent cleaning.Thermal Performance: Glass-lined tubes offer good thermal conductivity, allowing efficient heat transfer between the fluids. This results in improved heat exchange efficiency and overall system performance.Durability: Glass-lined tubes have high mechanical strength and durability, capable of withstanding high pressures and temperature differentials. They can withstand thermal shocks and fluctuations without experiencing damage or compromising the integrity of the heat exchanger.Versatility: Glass-lined tubes can be used with a wide range of fluids, including corrosive and high-temperature liquids. This versatility makes them suitable for diverse applications across various industries.By using glass-lined tubes in shell and tube heat exchangers, the integrity of the equipment is maintained while ensuring effective and reliable heat transfer. If you have any other questions, please click the pinecone on the right side of the screen and feel free to contact our product experts for a more comprehensive answer.\"}', '114.217.196.6', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/108.0.5359.95 Safari/537.36', 1685512301),
(625, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/edit', 'faq-编辑', '{\"id\":\"2\",\"enable\":\"1\",\"title\":\"\",\"en_title\":\"Why are silicon carbide tubes used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube shell and tube heat exchangers?\",\"content\":\"\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea Said,\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"Silicon carbide tubes are used as heat exchange tubes in shell and tube heat exchangers due to several key reasons:High Temperature Resistance: Silicon carbide exhibits exceptional resistance to high temperatures. It can withstand extreme heat without deforming or experiencing a significant loss in mechanical properties. This makes silicon carbide tubes suitable for heat exchangers operating in high-temperature applications.Corrosion Resistance: Silicon carbide is highly resistant to chemical corrosion. It can withstand exposure to corrosive substances such as acids, alkalis, and aggressive chemicals. This corrosion resistance ensures the long-term durability and integrity of the heat exchanger, even in challenging operating environments.Thermal Conductivity: Silicon carbide possesses excellent thermal conductivity, enabling efficient heat transfer between the fluids in the heat exchanger. This results in enhanced heat exchange performance, improved energy efficiency, and reduced operating costs.Thermal Shock Resistance: Silicon carbide exhibits exceptional resistance to thermal shocks and rapid temperature changes. It can withstand sudden temperature differentials without cracking or experiencing mechanical failure. This attribute is crucial in applications where the heat exchanger may encounter frequent or significant temperature variations.Mechanical Strength: Silicon carbide tubes have high mechanical strength and hardness. They can withstand high pressures and maintain their structural integrity under demanding conditions. This ensures the reliability and longevity of the heat exchanger, reducing the need for frequent maintenance or replacement.Wide Chemical Compatibility: Silicon carbide is chemically inert and has excellent compatibility with a broad range of fluids, including corrosive and reactive substances. This versatility makes it suitable for diverse industrial applications where the heat exchanger comes into contact with different fluids.The use of silicon carbide tubes in shell and tube heat exchangers offers exceptional performance, durability, and reliability in challenging operating environments. If you have any other questions, please click the pinecone on the right side of the screen and feel free to contact our product experts for a more comprehensive answer.\"}', '114.217.196.6', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/108.0.5359.95 Safari/537.36', 1685512357),
