(681, 1, 'admin', '/admin/Faq/edit', 'faq-编辑', '{\"id\":\"47\",\"enable\":\"1\",\"title\":\"\",\"en_title\":\"If your process medium contains Salts, why is Wuxi Repicea glass-lined shell-and-tube heat exchanger and silicon carbide heat exchanger a better choice for you?\",\"content\":\"\",\"en_content\":\"Repicea said,\",\"rich_content\":\"1\",\"en_rich_content\":\"If your process medium contains salts, selecting Wuxi Repicea&#039;s glass-lined shell-and-tube heat exchangers or silicon carbide heat exchangers offers several advantages:Excellent Salt Resistance: Both glass-lined and silicon carbide heat exchangers provided by Wuxi Repicea demonstrate exceptional resistance to salts. Glass-lined heat exchangers feature a durable glass lining that acts as a protective barrier against corrosive salts, preventing damage to the metal surface. Silicon carbide heat exchangers, being highly resistant to a wide range of chemicals, including salts, offer excellent resistance to salt-related corrosion. By choosing our heat exchangers, you can effectively handle salt-containing process media without concerns about corrosion or equipment deterioration.Chemical Compatibility: Glass-lined and silicon carbide heat exchangers exhibit high chemical compatibility with various salts. The glass lining in glass-lined heat exchangers provides excellent resistance to salt solutions, including both organic and inorganic salts. Silicon carbide, being a robust ceramic material, showcases exceptional resistance to a broad range of chemicals, including salts. This chemical compatibility ensures that the heat exchangers maintain their integrity and performance when exposed to salt-containing process streams.Durability and Longevity: The salt resistance of glass-lined and silicon carbide heat exchangers translates into enhanced durability and longevity. These heat exchangers are designed to withstand the corrosive effects of salts over extended periods, offering reliable and long-lasting performan