(824, 1, 'admin', '/admin/products.Products/edit', 'Unknown(edit)', '{\"id\":\"21\",\"parent_id\":\"1\",\"layout\":\"horizontal\",\"name\":\"product_21\",\"en_name\":\"New Type External Glass Lined Shell and Tube Heat Exchanger\",\"desc\":\"\",\"en_desc\":\"\",\"detail\":\"New Type External Glass Lined Shell and Tube Heat Exchanger\",\"en_detail\":\"For the external glass lined tubular heat exchanger produced by our company, the outer wall of the shell side and heat exchange tube is coated with glass lined anticorrosive coating. The tube plate is also made of steel lined molded PFA tube plate, sealed with filler threads, sealed with a single piece, and disassembled with a single piece. Compared with the glass lined tubular heat exchanger with material passing through the tube side, due to the large space of the material side, it is more suitable for gas phase materials, which is more conducive to gas saturation, heat exchange and final discharge in the cavity. When the heat exchange medium is used in the tube side, a jacket is also set outside, and the heat exchange medium can also be used in the jacket, so that the materials can fully exchange heat inside and outside. Traditional glass lined floating head tubular heat exchanger generally adopts glass lined tube sheet explosive enamel or PTFE tube sheet, which is easy to leak in case of high-pressure working condition, high maintenance cost, and too troublesome to disassemble and assemble. The same heat exchange area is larger. Compared with traditional glass lined floating head tubular heat exchanger, it is more resistant to pressure, and it is not easy to shake and indunce enamel bursting when gas enters. It also saves the user&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;#039;s use cost.\",\"image_small\":\"\",\"image_mid\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230426\\/83f0684ba3fb6a0314a07d6f0ec8b362e17bc86f.png\",\"image_large\":\"\\/storage\\/default\\/20230529\\/69b83984b93dd30dd5aa2bab4dd6a918707f8d6c.png\",\"carousel\":[\"\\/storage\\/defaul